# Lovable → Next.js reference

When the user asks to align UI with Lovable, or when editing files under `web/src/`:

## Source of truth

- **Reference (read-only):** `lovable/repo/src/` — cloned from Lovable GitHub export
- **Target (runnable app):** `web/src/` — Next.js App Router + Prisma

If `lovable/repo/src/` is missing, tell the user to follow `lovable/README.md` (GitHub connect + clone).

## How to port

1. Read the matching Lovable route/component first
2. Copy **layout, spacing, copy, colors** — not the router or store
3. Map TanStack Router `Link`/`useLocation` → Next.js `Link`/`usePathname`
4. Map Tailwind classes → existing CSS in `web/src/app/globals.css` (or add minimal CSS)
5. Keep server data (Prisma, `requireUser`, APIs) in Next pages — UI only from Lovable

## Do not copy as-is

- `lib/stacca-store.ts`, TanStack Router, Vite config
- Do not replace `web/` with the Lovable repo

## Key file pairs

| Lovable | web |
|---------|-----|
| `src/styles.css` | `src/app/globals.css` |
| `src/components/BottomNav.tsx` | `src/components/BottomNav.tsx` |
| `src/components/AppShell.tsx` | `src/components/AppShell.tsx` |
| `src/components/StaccaLogo.tsx` | `src/components/StaccaLogo.tsx` |
| `src/routes/index.tsx` | `src/app/(main)/page.tsx` |
| `src/routes/mese.tsx` | `src/app/(main)/mese/page.tsx` |
| `src/routes/profilo.tsx` | `src/app/(main)/profilo/page.tsx` |
| `src/routes/aggiungi.tsx` | `src/components/AggiungiForm.tsx` |
| `src/routes/login.tsx` | `src/app/login/page.tsx` |

## Brand

App name is **Stacca** everywhere — not Gino. Logo assets live in `web/public/stacca/`.
